President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Bob Work is being nominated for Deputy Secretary of Defense at the Department of Defense. He currently serves as the CEO of the Center for a New American Security and previously served as Under Secretary of the Navy. Cassandra Q. Butts is being nominated as Ambassador to the Commonwealth of The Bahamas at the Department of State. She is currently a Senior Advisor to the CEO of the Millennium Challenge Corporation and previously served as Deputy White House Counsel to President Obama. Matthew T. McGuire is being nominated as the United States Executive Director at the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development. He currently serves as the Director of the Office of Business Liaison at the Department of Commerce.